        "System.Description": "<div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">If two bonds are scanned with same redemption value then Vsoft recognises the second item as duplicate. Duplicate logic is based on amount which is causing the issue.&nbsp;</div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></div></div><div><br></div><div>1- Add Scan Bond Button in GL Credit transaction for adjustment during day 2 process\n<br></div>2.This scans the bond image but processes as a check, so it will not recalculate the Redemption value and will not generate a 1099 report.\n<br>3-This requires VSoft provides a Bond mode 3 functionality which is scanning a Bond as a check.\n<br><br>There is a Vsoft part to this enhancement request as well. \n<br><br>This will be a denorm and .dll fix. <hr>Reporter: Mohammed Mohiuddin<hr>External ID: 1912<hr>Components: <hr>Affiliates affected: NBA,NSB,VBC,ZFNB,ABT,CBT<hr>Original assignee: Trung Thai<hr>Found with a Test Case",
        "Microsoft.VSTS.TCM.SystemInfo": "<div>Zeus Teller&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Miscellaneous -&gt; GL Credit Transaction</div>",
        "Microsoft.VSTS.TCM.ReproSteps": "<div>1- Launch GL Credit Tranasaction</div><div>2- Select GL account from drop down and enter serial number</div><div>3- Click scan bond button</div><div>4- Scan atleast two bonds in the Vsoft scan bond window for the same redemption value</div><div><br></div><div>Result :&nbsp; After completing the scan for the second bond it is identified as a duplicate and system asks you remove the item before submitting.</div><div><br></div>",
        "System.Tags": "ALL AFFILIATES; ZEUS-8081"
    },
